article.description: Chandler Burks ran for two touchdowns, including the game-winner on a 1-yard sneak with 16 seconds left, and threw for another and Kennesaw State rallied to defeat Division II North Greenville 38-34 on Saturday.
article.headline: Burks leads Kennesaw to 38-34 win over North Greenville
article.linkText: Burks leads Kennesaw to 38-34 win over North Greenville
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Chandler Burks ran for two touchdowns, including the game-winner on a 1-yard sneak with 16 seconds left, and threw for another and Kennesaw State rallied to defeat Division II North Greenville 38-34 on Saturday. The Crusaders grabbed a 34-31 lead on a 33-yard touchdown pass from Will Hunter to Robbie Brown with 5:04 to play before Burks led a 12-play, 74-yard drive. Burks threw for 111 yards and had 22 carries for 100 yards. Kennesaw (3-1) rushed for 315 yards. Hunter threw for 283 yards and three touchdowns but also threw two interceptions. Ashton Heard had touchdowns rushing and receiving but the Crusaders (3-2), who were averaging 196 yards rushing, only picked up 47 on the ground. It was the second straight game the Owls held an opponent to less than 50 yards rushing. --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
